ading/Democratic}} |Democratic\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |58%<ref name=\"elections.msnbc.msn.com\">{{cite web|url=http://elections.msnbc.msn.com/ns/politics/2012/new-york/#.UKFgQuTAcwI |title=New York Election Results - President, Congress, Governor &#124; NBC News |publisher=Elections.msnbc.msn.com |date=November 5, 2012 |accessdate=May 21, 2013}}</ref>\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |Stephen Labate\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |42%<ref name=\"elections.msnbc.msn.com\"/>\n|-\n|[[United States House elections, 2014|2014]]\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |'''Steve Israel'''\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |Democratic\n|{{party shading/Democratic}} |54%<ref name=\"elections.msnbc.msn.com\">{{cite web|url=http://elections.msnbc.msn.com/ns/politics/2012/new-york/#.UKFgQuTAcwI |title=New York Election Results - President, Congress, Governor &#124; NBC News |publisher=Elections.msnbc.msn.com |date=November 5, 2012 |accessdate=May 21, 2013}}</ref>\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |Grant Lally\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|{{party shading/Republican}} |45%<ref name=\"elections.msnbc.msn.com\"/>\n|-\n{{s-end}}\n\n==Personal life==\nIsrael was divorced from his second wife, Marlene Budd, who is an acting NYS Supreme Court Judge.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsday.com/long-island/politics/steve-israel-marlene-budd-file-for-divorce-1.2907753 |title=Steve Israel, Marlene Budd file for divorce |publisher=Newsday |date=2011-05-27 |accessdate=2014-08-13}}</ref>\nThe sale of his marital home was and is the subject of some considerable controversy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsday.com/opinion/steve-israel-s-fortunate-home-sale-editorial-1.4098667 |title=Steve Israel's fortunate home sale - Editorial |publisher=Newsday |date=2012-10-10 |accessdate=2014-08-13}}</ref> This is due to the fact that he has received financial contributions from the lenders who gave him a favorable deal on a short sale of his marital home following his second divorce.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thehuntingtonian.com/2012/10/26/israels-lenders-gave-thousands-to-campaign/ |title=Israel\u2019s Lenders Gave Thousands To Campaign |publisher=The Huntingtonian |date=2012-10-26 |accessdate=2014-08-13}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Steve Israel}}\n* [http://www.house.gov/israel/ Congressman Steve Israel] official U.S. House site\n* [http://www.israelforcongress.com/ Steve Israel for Congress]\n* {{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/New_York/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Steve_Israel_%5BD-03%5D}}\n* {{CongLinks | congbio = i000057 | ballot = Steve_Israel | nndb = 093/000038976 | votesmart = 55440 | govtrack = 400195 | opencong = 400195 | rollcall = 10671 | politifact = | fec = H0NY02085 | opensecrets = N00013345 | assets = steve-israel | legistorm = 294/Rep_Steve_J_Israel_NY.html | followthemoney = | ontheissues = NY/Steve_Israel.htm | congress = steve-israel/1663 | worldcat = | cspan = 87911 | imdb = 2051240 | bloomberg = | nyt = | washpo = gIQAt0jCAP }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Rick Lazio]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from New York|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[New York's 2nd congressional district]]|years=2001\u20132013}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Peter T. King|Peter King]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Peter T. King|Peter King]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from New York|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[New York's 3rd congressional district]]|years=2013\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Chris Van Hollen]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chairperson of the  [[Democratic Congressional Campaign Committee]]|years=2011\u20132015}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ben R. Luj\u00e1n|Ben Luj\u00e1n]]<br>{{small|Designate}}}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Mike Honda]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of current members of the United State